bog pine
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 2
Definition:a widespread, bushy shrub of subalpine and alpine scrub,  found on boggy ground and well-drained stony terraces
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Halocarpus bidwilli</i>, previously <i>Dacrydium bidwilli, D. colensoi </i>; aka Bidwill's pine.
Citations
Date:  25/3/1875
Source:  Nelson Evening Mail
Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  The river was running over boulders, some of them as big as a house, and then between walls of rock,  the banks were being of the same boulders, covered with the worst scrub I ever saw - a kind of manuka, grass, trees and bog pine all twined together.
